sub_title: Consultant at ttopstart | Health & Life Sciences
summary:
As a consultant at ttopstart, I aspire to assist clients wherever needed in order for them to reach their goals such as the acquisition of funding and/or achieving collaborative success in research.

I would consider myself an optimist who can keep his cool in most situations, with a good dose of humour to keep the spirits up. My strengths lie in logical problem solving and creative thinking. I thrive when working with other people, often taking up the role of facilitator.

Having followed the MSc Nanobiology programme at Delft University of Technology and Erasmus MC, I possess skills in the fields of physics, mathematics, programming, and cell biology combined. While especially microbiological mechanisms have drawn my interest, I am excited to explore new grounds in the combination of microbiology and physics, or biologically-relevant programming in the ever-developing field of life sciences.
